data.content:
Three EF Core 10 breaking changes hit your code directly:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The `Action`-based overload lets you use normal C# control flow — no more `Expression.Lambda`/`Expression.Call` machinery.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — two changes

**a) Duplicate property names are now uniquified.** Since both `ShippingAddress` and `BillingAddress` have a `Street` property, EF 10 appends a numeric suffix to disambiguate. This generates a migration renaming columns.

**b) Nested complex types use the full path.** Your `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City` — it now maps to `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix:** Pin the old column names explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
    {
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street");
        // ... other properties
    });
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
    {
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street");
    });
});

// For nested complex types:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
    {
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
        {
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
        });
    });
});
```

Or let EF generate the rename migration — just verify the migration is correct before applying.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method (including `CommandReaderExecuting`) now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter:

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← NEW: redacted SQL safe for logging
    {
        // Use logCommandText for log output (constants may be redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the actual SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on this interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way — each gets the new `string logCommandText` parameter appended.
